reviews.text: Sushi is delicious, great vibe, the portion are really small though. Especially when you eat with 10 ladies you will need to order a lot more or triple up the amount of dishes. The tuna crunch biscuits are the must-order dish. Wish the wait staffs can be more attentive as we have 2 babies / toddlers on the table. Overall, good food and nice environment.

Very pleasant service from staff, very efficient in clearing empty plates from the table which kept our table nice and clean. 

We took our time looking through the menu and did not feel the pressure urging us to order which was nice. Wide range of food and drinks selection, everything looked amazing, and turned out that way too! Food seasoned well and sashimi as fresh as you can get.

It was a birthday celebration and so requested a birthday dessert when I made the reservation, staff was really attentive, knowing exactly when to bring the cake. No awkward moments of knowing there will be a little surprise coming along but having to wait for it and then pretending to be really surprise when you see it, let’s face it, it happens too often! Beautiful writing in gold (edible I assume?) dust on the dessert plate too. 

We were seated near the window side next to their outdoor seating area, view of the harbour would have been better if it wasn’t raining that night but that’s my only complain of the night really.

Honestly, the food itself is great, however I believe it was over priced. I actually love the location and window seat view of the harbour. 

Nevertheless, staff need to be trained better, just because we didn't order the most expensive dishes from the menu, the staff gave us a bad attitude when we were paying the bill (we still paid around $2300 for 4people), she did not say a single word of thank you and she did not stand next the person who had the bill, instead she shout across the table and say "over here" to the payer, with a straight face. We believe this was not professional at all. (bare in mind the service fee was charged at 10% of the bill)

Additionally, staff was chatting to each other loudly and laughing when we were asking for assistance. Overall if you are looking for a high end experience, there are plenty other options with less the price and better customer service.

Had the lunchtime omakase menu along with some other orders to share. Portion sizes are great and staff are super friendly and attentive. Authentic and fresh Japanese food. The view is great and outdoor seating is available as well, definitely should book a seat if fireworks are going to be out in the harbor. A definite treat.
Good food, a little pricey
Just a visit easy to access

由細到大去的大型商場，可惜近年實在太多旅客，星期六盡量不去。
落成於1966年3月22日之海運大厦，是九倉嘅旗艦商場，人流是尖沙咀區之最，因收益大，所以各方面的配套都務求做到最好，從60年代至今，已經歷四次大翻新，她位於九巴總站旁之廣場裝飾，是每年聖誕節各方面(如傳媒，市民)的焦點所在！
小時候的美好回憶，爸媽間中會帶我們幾姊弟來這裡的海天酒樓飲茶，飲完茶整家人就愛躲在商場裡四處悠幌嘆冷氣。
